Package: ForestForTrees
Title: Estimate Forest Size-Abundance Distributions from Remote Sensing Data
Version: 1.0.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Adam J.", "Eichenwald", email = "adam.eichenwald@maine.edu", role = c("aut", "cre")),
    person("John M.", "Grady", role = "aut"),
    person("Alyson", "East", role = "aut"),
    person("Noah", "Charney", role = "aut"),
    person("Sydne", "Record", role = "aut"))
Description: Provides a generalized, sensor-agnostic pipeline for estimating
    full forest size-abundance distributions from remotely sensed canopy data.
    The package automates Bayesian MCMC sampling, uncertainty propagation, and
    observational window detection using a truncated Pareto framework, and
    includes functionality for landscape-scale gridded mapping of forest
    structural parameters.
